details:
Case 211 is a 35 year-old female Filipino national who is a Singapore Long Term Visit Pass holder with no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is currently warded in an isolation room at NCID. She is linked to Case 142.

As she had been identified as a contact of Case 142, she was placed under quarantine on 9 March. She was referred to NCID on 13 March, and subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 14 March morning.

She stays at Crawford Lane.
